Hi @carlosperezb!

The behavior you're seeing is the "range" type filter processing a range of values.

For example if you search for `1 - 10`, the filter will return the value range of 1 to 10.

This also works with letters. For example, a search for `a - c` will result in entries from `aardvark` to `Czech`. Adding more letters will narrow the range, `India - napolis` (or the reverse range) `napolis - India` will return matches of words starting with `India` and ending with `napolis` (e.g. `Napa` (valley)).

Good news is that you can disable this type of search per column. Set the [`filter_excludeFilter` option](https://mottie.github.io/tablesorter/docs/index.html#widget-filter-exclude-filter) for that column, or all columns ([demo](https://jsfiddle.net/Mottie/bbxxomhx/916/)):

```js
$(function(){
  $("table").tablesorter({
    widgets: ["filter"],
    widgetOptions : {
      filter_excludeFilter : {
        // target a column by class name or column index (zero-based)
        0 : 'range',
        // target all columns; separate multiple filter types using spaces
        '.tablesorter-header' : 'fuzzy regex'
      }
    }
  });
});
```

